results of comparisons of risk-tailored CRC screening with no screening, and 
supported that risk-tailored screening was cost-effective. All of seven studies 
reported the ICERs of risk-tailored screening and age-based screening. 
Disparities in the discrimination of risk-prediction tool, accuracy of adopted 
techniques, uptake rate of screening and cost estimation impacted the 
cost-effectiveness.
CONCLUSIONS: Studies on the economic evaluation of risk-tailored CRC screening 
are limited, and current evidence is not sufficient to support the replacement 
of risk-tailored screening for traditional age-based screening.

